                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“praying always with all prayer and supplication in the Spirit, being watchful to this end with all perseverance and supplication for all the saints—”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:18 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“and for me, that utterance may be given to me, that I may open my mouth boldly to make known the mystery of the gospel, for which I am an ambassador in chains; that in it I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak.”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:19-20 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Albeit prayer is not a part of the armor of God.  It is as an invisible sheath covering the soldier entirely.  Each piece of armor along with the armor wearer need be saturated in prayer.  As we are tending to each piece of the armor it is imperative we are praying and seeking the God whose armor it is.  He has given us each piece and each one represents strength, power, victory but we must always be careful to not take advantage and allow Satan to put in our minds WE possess this power.  The power, the strength the victory is all Jesus’.  Prayer keeps this focus before us.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">One thing I know regarding service in the army of God, the longer I serve, the less I know and my dependence on Him must be greater in prayer.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">He tells us to pray always...with all prayer and supplication in the Spirit.  It is impossible to stay on our knees 24/7 physically.  We can spiritually.  We have opportunity to pray arrow prayers all day long, even in the night.  When having conversations our spirit can connect with His Spirit and we will not miss a beat of the conversation.  Praying as we drive, praying as we work, praying as we are shopping, playing golf, as we walk our neighborhood, whatever and where ever.  Our warfare is all around us each day, and our communication with God need be continual, praying always with all prayer.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Another realization I’ve had is God is not concerned with our words.  So often we hear, “I don’t know how to pray,  I can’t pray eloquently.  God doesn’t want eloquence, He desires sincerity.  It is okay if you feel you can’t pray correctly.  There is no incorrectly in sincerity with God.  He is listening to your heart not your words.  When we meet people we don’t always know what to say.  The more time we spend with them the easier it gets.  Same with God...He desires you to become conscious of His presence already with you.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Prayer is the heart of the armor of God, without prayer the armor is null and void.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Pray always with all prayers and supplication in the Spirit, being watchful to this end with all perseverance and supplication for all the saints and for us, that utterance may be given to us, that we may open our mouths boldly to make known the mystery of the gospel, for which we are ambassadors  in chains; that in it we may speak boldly, as we  ought to speak.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Today we close out 21 days of fasting and prayer.  We have contemplated 12 attributes of God reminding us of who it is that is really in charge, and who we serve.  Then the six pieces of armor He has provided to stand for Him against His and therefore our enemy, doing what He calls us to do in proclaiming the Gospel of Jesus Christ.  The culmination of the two is prayer.
                                                                            A quote I read gives a simple definition of prayer,  “paying attention to God.”  This speaks volumes.  The main point is we speak to Him, then we listen and follow Him.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our country is in great need for a mighty move of God Almighty.  We’ve had struggles in the past that God Himself delivered His people.  Those struggles don’t compare to what is on the horizon today.  God is all He says He is and everything is working according to His plan.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Please join your heart with the singer below and join in with prayer...<b>GOD BLESS YOU!</b>
                                                                        </p>
